Description: Low ring foot and floor sherd of Attic black glaze pottery skyphos; glazed black (misfired red in parts) on interior and exterior; reserved: resting surface and central disc on underside; plastic ring near centre of underside; broad red band on outer part of underside; inscriptions cut on floor and on underside.
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1886 / Naukratis. Part I., 1884-85 (pl. XXXIII, no. 378)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GA.1258)
